deletions.Query:
MERGE INTO deletions AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, $1[1] AS "_meta/op", $1[2] AS flow_published_at, $1[3] AS flow_document
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= 1 AND l.id <= 3
WHEN MATCHED AND r.flow_document='delete' THEN
	DELETE
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l."_meta/op" = r."_meta/op", l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at, l.flow_document = r.flow_document
WHEN NOT MATCHED and r.flow_document!='delete' THEN
	INSERT (id, "_meta/op", flow_published_at, flow_document)
	VALUES (r.id, r."_meta/op", r.flow_published_at, r.flow_document);

duplicate_keys_standard.Query:
MERGE INTO duplicate_keys_standard AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, $1[1] AS flow_published_at, $1[2] AS int, $1[3] AS str, $1[4] AS flow_document
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= 1 AND l.id <= 5
WHEN MATCHED AND r.flow_document='delete' THEN
	DELETE
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at, l.int = r.int, l.str = r.str, l.flow_document = r.flow_document
WHEN NOT MATCHED and r.flow_document!='delete' THEN
	INSERT (id, flow_published_at, int, str, flow_document)
	VALUES (r.id, r.flow_published_at, r.int, r.str, r.flow_document);

multiple_types.Query:
MERGE INTO multiple_types AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, NULLIF($1[1], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS array_int, $1[2] AS binary_field, $1[3] AS bool_field, $1[4] AS float_field, $1[5] AS flow_published_at, NULLIF($1[6], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS multiple, NULLIF($1[7], PARSE_JSON('null')) AS nested, $1[8] AS nullable_int, $1[9] AS str_field, $1[10] AS flow_document
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= 1 AND l.id <= 10
WHEN MATCHED AND r.flow_document='delete' THEN
	DELETE
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l.array_int = r.array_int, l.binary_field = r.binary_field, l.bool_field = r.bool_field, l.float_field = r.float_field, l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at, l.multiple = r.multiple, l.nested = r.nested, l.nullable_int = r.nullable_int, l.str_field = r.str_field, l.flow_document = r.flow_document
WHEN NOT MATCHED and r.flow_document!='delete' THEN
	INSERT (id, array_int, binary_field, bool_field, float_field, flow_published_at, multiple, nested, nullable_int, str_field, flow_document)
	VALUES (r.id, r.array_int, r.binary_field, r.bool_field, r.float_field, r.flow_published_at, r.multiple, r.nested, r.nullable_int, r.str_field, r.flow_document);

string_escaped_key.Query:
MERGE INTO string_escaped_key AS l
USING (
	SELECT $1[0] AS id, $1[1] AS counter, $1[2] AS flow_published_at, $1[3] AS flow_document
	FROM <uuid>
) AS r
ON 
	l.id = r.id AND l.id >= '\\he \\ '' " `llo`' AND l.id <= '\\he \\ '' " `llo`'
WHEN MATCHED AND r.flow_document='delete' THEN
	DELETE
WHEN MATCHED THEN
	UPDATE SET l.counter = r.counter, l.flow_published_at = r.flow_published_at, l.flow_document = r.flow_document
WHEN NOT MATCHED and r.flow_document!='delete' THEN
	INSERT (id, counter, flow_published_at, flow_document)
	VALUES (r.id, r.counter, r.flow_published_at, r.flow_document);
